Arp Commands		
Action		Command
Display ARP table		arp -a
Same as -a		arp -g
Display ARP table in verbose mode		arp -v
Specifies and internet address		arp inet_addr
Displays the ARP entries for the specified network interface		arp -N if_addr
Delete an IP address (arp -d 192.168.100.10)		arp -d
Add an entry to the ARP table (arp -s ADDRESS MAC_ADDRESS - Where ADDRESS is the address to be added and MAC_ADDRESS is the MAC address of the machine)		arp -s
Specifies a physical address		arp eth_addr
Specifies the internet address of the interface that needs modification		arp if_addr
		
Show local routes		route print
		
Get MAC Address		getmac /S <computername> /U domain\userÂ 
